snippet: House Republicans rejected a State Senate plans as well as the G.O.P. governor’s wishes.
abstract: House Republicans in Florida reject State Senate plan to expand Medicaid in state, and time has run out to draft compromise bill before Legislature leaves town; impasse leaves more than a million low-income Floridians without insurance; state must agree on plan to expand coverage by Jan 1, 2014, or it will lose $1 billion in federal Medicaid dollars.

byline.original: By LIZETTE ALVAREZ and CHRISTINE JORDAN SEXTON
byline.contributor: Lizette Alvarez reported from Miami, and Christine Jordan Sexton from Tallahassee, Fla.

lead_paragraph: House Republicans rejected a State Senate plans as well as the G.O.P. governor’s wishes.

headline.main: Florida Runs Out of Time on Medicaid
headline.print_headline: Florida Runs Out of Time On Medicaid
